Note: The Protected Payment Base is not a contract value and is not available for withdrawal like a cash value. Your actual contract value and death benefit will decrease with each withdrawal. 


Downside protectionBecause your Protected Payment Base is the highest value your contract reaches on any contract anniversary date after the GLWB option is purchased, it is locked and protected against market losses.


Guaranteed lifetime incomeWhen you begin taking income after reaching age 65, you can receive 5% of your locked-in Protected Payment Base for life (4.5% for joint life rider)—even if market volatility, income withdrawals, and annuity fees reduce your contract value to zero. 


When you purchase the GLWB, your Protected Payment Base isestablished and locked against market downturns. 









