Penalty free withdrawals2


New York Life Secure Term Choice Fixed Annuity II

Each policy year, you may withdraw the greatest of:

10% of the accumulation value as of the previous anniversary, or
10% of the current accumulation value, or
100% of the gain earned in the policy. (For policies with a premium amount of $100,000 or more. Not available in New York.)

Required minimum distributions (RMD):
Qualifying RMD amounts that exceed the free withdrawal amount are not subject to surrender charges14




MassMutual Stable Voyage℠


First contract year: Up to 10% of the contract value as determined at the time the first withdrawal request is processed
Contract years two and later: Up to 10% of the contract value calculated as of the last business day of the previous contract year
Required minimum distributions (RMD): 
Qualifying RMD amounts for an IRA or a qualified plan that exceed the free withdrawal amount are not subject to surrender charges




Midland National LiveWell Guarantee Annuity


After the first contact year: Withdraw up to 5% (not cumulative) of the accumulation value per year (market value adjustment2,10 and surrender charges do not apply)
Required minimum distributions (RMD): 
Qualifying RMD amounts that exceed the penalty-free  5% withdrawal amount are subject to surrender charges or market value adjustment




